    body
        div.container
            div.col-md-12
                img(src="media/logo/nourriture.svg" class="img-responsive")

            div.col-md-12
                p.box.
                    Nourriture is a community web-app based on recipe sharing and permits to connect people with ingredients. With Nourriture, innovative food suppliers and
                    app developers have the most comprehensive platform
                    from which they can quickly and accurately create relevant
                    tools for consumers to make informed decisions about food.The backend is forged in ExpressJS and data are stored in a MongoDB database.
                    The front end is forged in AngularJS, Bootstrap and Jade. An Android Application will soon be available.

                h1.t-center Documentation

                h3 Api Documentation

                p.box.
                    For a complete documentation on how to use our API, you can click on the link below :<br>
                    <a href="/doc-models" class="t-center">Nourriture API 0.1.0</a>
                h3 OAuth 2.0 Documentation

                div.box
                    p.
                        OAuth allows an end user's account information to be used by third-party services. It will permit to share our API to other developers.
                        <br><br>
                        The documentation to use it with our API is available here : <a href="doc-auth/#api-OAuth">Nourriture OAuth2.0 API 0.1.0</a><br><br>
                        Here is a little summary of the steps to follow in order to use OAuth2.0 with our website :

                    ol
                        li First create a new client
                            
                        li.
                            Enter this URL in a web browser<span class="wb"> http://localhost:3000/api/oauth2/authorize?client_id=<strong>id_client</strong>&response_type=code&redirect_uri=http://localhost:3000</span><br>
                            Where <strong>id_client</strong> is the id of the user's client<br>
                            The url will give you back an authorization code.

                        li.
                            Use this POST endpoint to have a token <a href="doc-auth/#api-OAuthToken-createToken">api/oauth2/token</a>. <br>
                            You need to pass <strong>name of client</strong> and <strong>secret of the client</strong> with <strong>Basic</strong>


                        li. 
                            After retrieving the token just create an authorization header with our custom token authorization :<br>
                            <code>Authorization : Topkek eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJfaWQiOiI1NjJhMmJhMzEzOTRhMjdiMWI1YTl</code>

